# unmatched_close_paren_test.deor
# Exercises check_paren_balance.deor's extra-')' case. Before this check existed,
# an unmatched extra ')' drove paren_depth negative, which silently disabled
# check_keyword_in_parens (it only fires when paren_depth > 0) for the rest of
# the file — the stray token was otherwise ignored and the file built anyway.

fn void main()
	int total = 1 + 2)
	print(total)

# expect-error:
# line 8: variable ')' - ')' has no matching '(' before it
